data.title: Cypriot policewoman honoured by King Charles III
data.description: British bases Police Chief Inspector Maria Atalioti is among the first woman awarded an Overseas Territories Police Medal by King Charles III on the New Year Honours List. She is also one of only two to receive the King’s award. The prestigious award was given to the 25-year Cypriot police veteran for her outstanding work and dedication to her job. The Akrotiri-based chief inspector is the most senior female officer in SBA Police history.
